&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;How would you design an Hbase table
  for many-to-many association between
  two entities, for example Student and
  Course?&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;I would define two tables:&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;Student: student id student data
  (name, address, ...) courses (use
  course ids as column qualifiers here) &lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;Course: course id course data (name,
  syllabus, ...) students (use student
  ids as column qualifiers here)&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;This schema gives you fast access to
  the queries, show all classes for a
  student (student table, courses
  family), or all students for a class
  (courses table, students family).&lt;/p&gt;
